Hope of Ghirapur is turning out to be an intriguing puzzle. On one hand it really feels grounded and has control on card, so it feels like a solid voltron choice. On the other hand it feels like it could just as easily supplement a stax plan and be played almost politically. I'm unsure of what direction I want to go with it for the article.
